An anonymous reader writes "The BBC is reporting that the [0]English
Premier Football League has launched a lawsuit against YouTube and its
owner Google, claiming unspecified damages. The league is sitting on
high-profile content valued at $5.4 billion over the next 3 years in a
recent series of auctions. This will be the [1]second major suit against
YouTube since Google's purchase."

