    1. http://www.nytimes.com/2007/05/06/world/europe/07francecnd.html


+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Mathematicians Design Invisible Tunnel                             |
|   from the worms-need-light-too dept.                              |
|   posted by kdawson on Sunday May 06, @18:05 (Math)                |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/06/1851217      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

New calculations show how to make an electromagnetic "wormhole" — a
[0]tube that is invisible from the sides but allows light to shine down
the center. The practical applications are a ways off, as even the design
of a [1]spherical invisibility cloak has not advanced beyond working (in
theory) for a single wavelength of visible light.

