+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| You Can't Oppose Copyright and Support Open Source                 |
|   from the baby-with-the-bathwater dept.                           |
|   posted by kdawson on Sunday May 06, @19:13 (GNU is Not Unix)     |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/06/2114258          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Reader [0]gbulmash sends us to his essay on the [1]fallacy of those who
would abolish copyright. The argument is that without copyright granting
an author the right to set licensing terms for his/her work, the GPL
could not be enforced. The essay concludes that if you support the GPL or
any open source license (other than public domain), your fight should be
not about how to abolish copyright, but how to reform copyright.

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/06/2114258

Links:
    0. http://www.brainhandles.com/
    1. http://www.brainhandles.com/2007/05/06/should-copyright-be-abolished/



